# TapTrack — Payment Tracking App

A mobile app that records card-tap payments and provides daily spending summaries with zero data leakage.

---

## Tech Stack Recommendation

| Layer | Choice | Why |
|-------|--------|-----|
| **OS Target** | **iOS first, Android built-in** | iOS has stricter security sandbox. Cross-platform framework gives Android free. |
| **Language** | **TypeScript** | Type safety catches bugs at compile time. Self-documenting types replace comments. |
| **Framework** | **React Native (Expo)** | Cross-platform from day one. Expo provides secure storage, biometrics, and camera APIs out of the box. |
| **Local Database** | **WatermelonDB** (SQLite under the hood) | Fast, encrypted, reactive queries. Data never leaves the device. |
| **Encryption** | **react-native-encrypted-storage** + **expo-crypto** | AES-256 encryption for all stored payment data. |
| **Auth** | **expo-local-authentication** | Biometric (Face ID / fingerprint) lock — no passwords to leak. |
| **State Management** | **Zustand** | Minimal boilerplate, TypeScript-first, no Redux ceremony. |
| **UI** | **React Native Paper** (Material Design 3) | Polished components, dark mode, accessibility built-in. |
| **Testing** | **Jest + React Native Testing Library** | Unit + integration tests for every data layer. |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Why not native Swift/Kotlin?** React Native with Expo gives us both platforms with one codebase, TypeScript's type system makes code self-documenting (matching your clean-code goal), and the security libraries are production-grade. If performance bottlenecks appear later, we can eject specific modules to native.

