## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph Presentation["🖥️ Presentation Layer"]
        A["HomeScreen"]
        B["AddPaymentScreen"]
        C["DailySummaryScreen"]
        D["SettingsScreen"]
    end

    subgraph Logic["⚙️ Business Logic Layer"]
        E["usePayments hook"]
        F["useDailySummary hook"]
        G["useBudgetAlerts hook"]
        H["PaymentValidator"]
    end

    subgraph Data["💾 Data Layer (Encrypted)"]
        I["PaymentRepository"]
        J["CategoryRepository"]
        K["WatermelonDB + AES-256"]
    end

    subgraph Security["🔒 Security Layer"]
        L["BiometricGate"]
        M["EncryptionService"]
        N["SecureStorageService"]
    end

    A --> E
    B --> E
    C --> F
    A --> G
    E --> H
    H --> I
    F --> I
    I --> K
    J --> K
    K --> M
    L --> A
    M --> N
end
```

### Layer Responsibilities

| Layer | Responsibility | Security Rule |
|-------|---------------|---------------|
| **Presentation** | UI rendering, user input, animations | No raw data in component state — only formatted display values |
| **Business Logic** | Validation, calculations, summaries | All amounts handled as integers (cents) to avoid float errors |
| **Data** | CRUD operations, queries, caching | Every read/write goes through encryption service |
| **Security** | Auth, encryption, secure storage | App locks after 30s background. Biometric required to unlock. |

---

## Data Models

```typescript
// All monetary values stored as integers (cents) to prevent floating-point errors

interface Payment {
  id: string;                    // UUID v4
  amountInCents: number;         // e.g., 1599 = $15.99
  merchantName: string;          // "Starbucks"
  category: PaymentCategory;     // enum: FOOD, TRANSPORT, SHOPPING, etc.
  cardLastFourDigits: string;    // "4521" — only last 4, never full card number
  timestamp: number;             // Unix epoch ms
  note?: string;                 // optional user note
  isRecurring: boolean;          // flag for subscriptions
}

enum PaymentCategory {
  FOOD = "FOOD",
  TRANSPORT = "TRANSPORT",
  SHOPPING = "SHOPPING",
  ENTERTAINMENT = "ENTERTAINMENT",
  BILLS = "BILLS",
  HEALTH = "HEALTH",
  OTHER = "OTHER",
}

interface DailySummary {
  date: string;                  // "2026-04-14"
  totalSpentInCents: number;
  transactionCount: number;
  categoryBreakdown: Record<PaymentCategory, number>;
  largestPayment: Payment;
  averagePaymentInCents: number;
}

interface UserPreferences {
  currency: string;              // "USD", "INR", "EUR"
  dailyBudgetInCents: number;    // alert threshold
  biometricEnabled: boolean;
  darkModeEnabled: boolean;
}
```

> [!CAUTION]
> **We NEVER store**: full card numbers, CVVs, PINs, bank account numbers, or any PCI-regulated data. Only the last 4 digits of the card are stored for identification purposes.

---

## Security Strategy — Zero Data Leakage

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A["App Launch"] --> B{"Biometric\nVerified?"}
    B -- Yes --> C["Decrypt DB Key\nfrom Secure Enclave"]
    B -- No --> D["Lock Screen\n3 attempts max"]
    C --> E["Open Encrypted DB"]
    E --> F["App Ready"]
    F --> G{"App goes to\nBackground?"}
    G -- ">30 seconds" --> A
    G -- "<30 seconds" --> F
    D -- "3 failures" --> H["Wipe Session\nRequire Re-auth"]
```

### Security Measures

| Threat | Mitigation |
|--------|------------|
| **Data at rest** | AES-256 encrypted SQLite database. Key stored in iOS Keychain / Android Keystore. |
| **Data in memory** | Sensitive fields cleared from state on background. No logging of payment amounts. |
| **Screenshots** | `react-native-screen-capture` blocks screenshots and screen recording. |
| **Rooted/Jailbroken devices** | Detection via `expo-device` — warn user, optionally block app. |
| **No cloud sync** | All data stays on-device. No analytics, no telemetry, no third-party SDKs that phone home. |
| **Clipboard attacks** | Payment amounts are never copied to clipboard. |
| **Debug builds** | Production builds strip all `console.log`. Hermes bytecode prevents easy reverse engineering. |

