## Clean Code Conventions

Following your requirement — **function names ARE the documentation**:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — Name tells the full story, no comment needed
function calculateDailyTotalInCents(payments: Payment[]): number

function filterPaymentsByDate(payments: Payment[], targetDate: Date): Payment[]

function encryptAndStorePayment(payment: Payment): Promise<void>

function buildCategoryBreakdown(payments: Payment[]): Record<PaymentCategory, number>

function validatePaymentAmount(amountInCents: number): ValidationResult

function authenticateWithBiometrics(): Promise<AuthResult>

function formatCentsToDisplayCurrency(cents: number, currency: string): string


// ❌ BAD — Vague name needs a comment to explain
function process(data: any): any  // processes payment data ???

function calc(p: Payment[]): number  // calculates... what?

function handle(e: Event): void  // handles... how?
```

### Naming Rules We'll Follow

| Element | Convention | Example |
|---------|-----------|---------|
| Functions | verb + noun + context | `fetchPaymentsByDateRange` |
| Booleans | is/has/should prefix | `isRecurring`, `hasExceededBudget` |
| Handlers | handle + event | `handlePaymentSubmit` |
| Constants | SCREAMING_SNAKE | `MAX_RETRY_ATTEMPTS` |
| Types | PascalCase, descriptive | `PaymentCategory`, `DailySummary` |
| Files | PascalCase components, camelCase utils | `PaymentCard.tsx`, `formatCurrency.ts` |

